&lt;h1 id="cities-and-ambition"&gt;Cities and Ambition&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;May 2008&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Great cities attract ambitious people. You can sense it when you walk around one. In a hundred subtle ways, the city sends you a message: you could do more; you should try harder.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The surprising thing is how different these messages can be. New York tells you, above all: you should make more money. There are other messages too, of course. You should be hipper. You should be better looking. But the clearest message is that you should be richer.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>Jessica Livingston</title><link>https://linguista.cn/paul_graham/essays_en/jessica/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://linguista.cn/paul_graham/essays_en/jessica/</guid><description>&lt;p&gt;→ &lt;a href="https://linguista.cn/paul_graham/essays_zh/jessica/"&gt;中文版本&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
