&lt;h1 id="jessica-livingston"&gt;Jessica Livingston&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;November 2015&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A few months ago an article about Y Combinator said that early on it had been a &amp;ldquo;one-man show.&amp;rdquo; It&amp;rsquo;s sadly common to read that sort of thing. But the problem with that description is not just that it&amp;rsquo;s unfair. It&amp;rsquo;s also misleading. Much of what&amp;rsquo;s most novel about YC is due to Jessica Livingston. If you don&amp;rsquo;t understand her, you don&amp;rsquo;t understand YC. So let me tell you a little about Jessica.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>The Origins of Wokeness</title><link>https://linguista.cn/paul_graham/essays_en/woke/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://linguista.cn/paul_graham/essays_en/woke/</guid><description>&lt;p&gt;→ &lt;a href="https://linguista.cn/paul_graham/essays_zh/woke/"&gt;中文版&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
